Open a terminal.
Find the process ID (PID) using the port:
bash
lsof -i :port_number
Alternatively, you can use netstat to see what process is using the port:
bash
sudo netstat -tulpn | grep port_number
Terminate the process using its PID:
bash
kill -9 PID
A quicker command to kill the process directly is:
bash
sudo fuser -k port_number/tcp


